Visit patek.com to view this four part series that explores the mechanics of the Sky Moon Tourbillon. In total, this extraordinary timepiece combines 12 fascinating complications, including a tourbillon and a minute repeater that strikes on cathedral gongs.

The reverse side of the case reveals the course of the moon, with sidereal time, sky chart, phases, and orbit of the moon.

#PatekTime

With its sporty casual and elegant look, the Aquanaut is a favorite amongst international travelers, constantly on-the-go.

The new Aquanaut Luce Travel Time presents itself as a true travel companion.

It features two hour hands – one pierced for home time, the other solid for local time.

When changing time zones, the hour hand for local time may be set forwards or backwards by increments of one hour using the crown.

#PatekTime #Aquanaut #AquanautLuce

The new Ref. 5236 In-line Perpetual Calendar opens up a new chapter in the storied history of Patek Philippe calendar timepieces, with the addition of a totally new perpetual calendar wristwatch with an innovative patented one-line display that displays the day, the date, and the month on a single line. 

While seemingly simple, the in-line display presented a highly complex technical challenge and the development of a new movement (caliber 31-260 PS QL) for which three patent applications have been filed.  

#PatekPhilippe #PerpetualCalendar #PatekTime

The new Ref. 5236 In-line Perpetual Calendar houses the new self-winding movement caliber 31-260 PS QL. PS for ‘petite seconde’ [subsidiary seconds] and QL for ‘quantième perpétuel en ligne’ [in-line perpetual calendar]). The seemingly simple in-line display presented a highly complex technical challenge and development of three patented innovations.

The movement consists of 503 parts, 298 of which are dedicated to the perpetual calendar function. In the assembly process, a ‘test’ dial is used to ensure the optimal functionality of the in-line display.

node.text:
With the introduction of these new timepieces, Patek Philippe creates an eclectic bouquet of novelties - ranging from the much awaited, casual elegant Nautilus collection, new additions to the timelessly elegant Calatrava collection, a totally new Grand Complication and an addition to the ingenious patented Annual Calendar collection.
 
The introduction of these new references reflect the Manufacture’s extensive mastery of technical complexity, without sacrificing a perfect aesthetic.

“If you want to preserve your independence, you must have a fantastic product, and to have a fantastic product, you have to control the quality that goes inside. To do that, you have to do it yourself. We have been evolving in terms of quantity, in terms of complexity, and we needed more space, more tools, more people, more machines.

This is why we decided at one point, in 2013, to think about the future of Patek Philippe, by having a new building.”

Thierry Stern, President, Patek Philippe

node.text:
The Patek Philippe Diamond Ribbon Ref. 4968 created on the inspiration of a spiralling gymnast’s ribbon, requires unique techniques to produce the case design and meticulous diamond setting savoir-faire, perfectly balancing technical mechanical mastery and feminine allure.

Manually wound mechanical movement caliber 215 PS LU.

node.text:
With its pure lines, the Calatrava collection has embodied simplicity and timeless elegance since 1932. It is one of the finest symbols of the Patek Philippe style that continuously charms new generations of watch lovers.

In April 2021, Patek Philippe introduced a new design and movement to one of its most iconic models, launching the Calatrava “Clous de Paris” Ref. 6119. 

It is now time to explore these legendary models...

#PatekTime
#PatekCalatrava

Elegance through the ages.

The Calatrava established itself as the quintessential classic round wristwatch. Its pure style was inspired by the Bauhaus movement - a German art school which focussed on reducing design down to its most essential elements: “form follows function”.

The manufacture’s first Calatrava model was introduced in 1932 with Ref. 96. Followed in 1934, by the Ref. 96D with the first “Clous de Paris” or hobnail pattern on the bezel and with the same manually wound caliber 12-120 movement.

In 1985, Patek Philippe introduced the legendary Ref. 3919. This model was produced for over 20 years.  Since then, the model has been repeatedly reinterpreted in numerous versions for both ladies and men. 

In April 2021, Patek Philippe has endowed this Calatrava with a fresh outlook by updating its iconic design in a very contemporary manner with the introduction of Ref. 6119.

#PatekCalatrava

node.text:
The new Calatrava Ref. 6119 pays tribute to the legendary Ref. 3919 (1985).

The new design distinguishes itself mainly with a slightly larger diameter of 39 mm. It reflects the changing preferences of our era and emphasizes its presence on the wrist without compromising the slender elegance of its case. 

Further elements were reworked: the applied faceted “obus” markers in 18K gold accentuate the timelessly sleek aspect of the dial with a larger diameter. The round bezel is decorated with a “guilloché” hobnail pattern. Finally, the shape of the strap lugs was revised, in part inspired by the original Calatrava model, the Ref. 96.

Ref. 6119 in rose gold combines a rose gold case with silvery grained dial as well as applied hour markers and hands in rose gold. It is worn on a polished alligator strap in chocolate brown featuring a rose gold prong buckle.

node.text:
Calatrava Ref. 6119 in white gold subtly plays with light with its combination of contrasting finishes: a charcoal gray dial with a vertical satin finish punctuated by the snailed subsidiary seconds dial. 
The applied hour makers and hands are made of the same metal as the case. 

The new manually wound movement, caliber 30-255 PS marries finesse and performance, delivering a power reserve of 65 hours.

#PatekTime

node.text:
With the introduction of a totally new manually wound movement, the Ref. 6119 established a new milestone in the history of Patek Philippe’s most famous timepiece collection. It offers a rare opportunity to present a new movement that enriches the broad range of movements crafted by the manufacture.

The new caliber 30-255 PS has an inside case diameter of 30.4 mm and an unchanged height of 2.55 mm. To preserve the height of 2.55 mm of the ultra-thin caliber 215 but with an increased power reserve, the engineers of the manufacture implemented several ingenious solutions, including two mainspring barrels in a parallel arrangement.

It is exceptionally robust and powerful, delivering a power reserve of 65 hours, or nearly three days. 

#PatekTime
#PatekCalatrava

The architecture of the new base movement is carefully aligned with ancestral traditions, where every function, has its own bridge. Behind the sapphire-crystal case back, the caliber 30-255 PS thus reveals six elegantly shaped bridges that are finished to the most exacting horological traditions. 

This includes Geneva striping as well as chamfered and polished edges. The new manually wound movement harmoniously pairs aesthetics and performance. It celebrates its debut in the Calatrava Ref. 6119.

The manually wound movement reinforces the personal bond between the timepiece and its owner, through the daily ritual of winding the watch. 

#PatekTime
#PatekCalatrava

“You never actually own a Patek Philippe, you merely look after it for the next generation”. 

Launched in 1996, the “Generations” campaign has proven to be timeless and universally acclaimed. Its ongoing success and extraordinary longevity was founded on the unique emotional bond between a parent and a child.

#PatekTime 
#PatekGenerations

This new flagship of the Patek Philippe style reinforces the Manufacture’s grand classics; the round bezel of the Calatrava Ref. 6119 is decorated with the “Clous de Paris”, also known as a hobnail pattern and exhibits a slightly wider case of 39mm that frames the box-form sapphire crystal glass.

node.text:
Elegance in beautiful harmony.

Ladies’ Calatrava timepieces offer a powerful combination of aesthetic refinement and horological flair, all powered by the ultra-thin self-winding mechanical movement caliber 240.

The bezel of the Calatrava Ref. 4997/200 in white gold is lit up by 76 round-cut internally flawless Top Wesselton diamonds (~0.52 ct). The stunning blue “guilloché” dial plate is coated with several successive layers of transparent midnight blue lacquer creating a subtle depth effect.

Ref. 7200 in delicate rose gold is a ladies’ wristwatch fully focused on hours and minutes. The Officer’s-style case epitomizes timelessness in classic, feminine perfection.
The diamond-set version, Ref. 7200/200 ushers in a new form of gemsetting artistry that adds extra brilliance to the diamonds’ fire. The technique, named Flamme® gemsetting, emphasizes the unique skills of the Patek Philippe manufacture.

#PatekTime
#PatekCalatrava

The unique diamond setting on the Patek Philippe Diamond Ribbon “Joaillerie” Ref. 4978/400 in white gold wraps around the case and dial like the gymnast ribbon; the spiral composed of 679 brilliant-cut diamonds of graduated size (~3.99 ct). 

A further 48 diamonds adorn the lugs (~0.17 ct), 16 diamonds ornament the crown (~0.03 ct) and 27 diamonds: (~0.21 ct). With a total 770 diamonds (~4.4 ct.) the Ref. 4978/400G is a true reflection of the beauty of the gemsetter’s technique.

Beneath this radiant exterior beats the caliber 240 ultra-thin self-winding movement, enabling the watch to maintain its slim, elegant profile.

#PatekTime
#PatekCalatrava

node.text:
Calatrava Ref. 5227 is powered by the self-winding caliber 324 S C and features a sapphire crystal display back protected with a hinged dust cover. 

With precision craftmanship, the cover is attached to the case back by an ingeniously concealed hinge on the inside, making it invisible to even renowned watch connoisseurs. Even Philippe Stern could not detect the hinge that opens the dust cover when the watch was first presented to him by his son, Thierry Stern.

With its refined and pure lines and manually wound movement (caliber 215 PS), the Calatrava Ref. 5196 is recognized as the very essence of the round wristwatch and one of the finest symbols of the Patek Philippe style. Supremely elegant, it charms each new generation of watch lovers by its timeless understated perfection.

node.text:
The Calatrava timeless elegance further enhanced by unique rare handcrafts techniques.

Enamelling is one of the most high-risk of the rare handcrafts. The precarious fusing of powdered glass at ultra-high temperatures can produce heart-breaking results, but - when successful - the result is luminous beauty.

Such is the case on the dial of the Calatrava Ref. 5088. The power of the black enamel contrasts with the clarity of the hand-engraved arabesques creating a dramatic play on light, reflecting every detail of this exquisite timepiece.

Calatrava Ref. 5297 in white gold features a similarly intense dial this time in black ebony opaline, adorned by internally flawless Top Wesselton diamond hour markers. Self-winding mechanical movement caliber 324 S C.
